citation: Proclamation under the Property Agents and Land Transactions Act 2005 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Property Agents and Land Transactions Act 2005

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Property Agents and Land Transactions Act 2005 fix 1 December 2006 as the day on which the provisions of that Act, except Part 10 , commence.

20 November 2006

W. J. E. COX

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

STEVEN KONS

Minister for Justice and Workplace Relations

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 29 November 2006

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Justice.
